&gt;
&gt; fork=&quot;true&quot; is not only there to get rid of Ant&#39;s classes, but also to
&gt; isolate test cases from each other - tests that load native libraries
&gt; and fail because a different test has already loaded them, tests that
&gt; use Singletons and rely on a certain state and so on.
&gt;
&gt; Many things, the Singleton case above for example, can be solved by
&gt; writing tests properly, but this was one additional reason to
&gt; implement forking in &lt;junit&gt; as it is.
